ArcelorMittal, Harmony, Impala Platinum: South Africa Stock Market Preview

-- B y   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 
2011-08-15T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/arcelormittal-harmony-impala-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index gained 336.2, or 1.1
percent, to 29,826.4 in Johannesburg.  ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd. (ACL)  : Africa’s largest
steelmaker said a letter declaring force majeure was issued on
Aug. 11 because the company could lose around 400,000 metric
tons of steel output due to a structural failure at its gas
cleaning plant in Newcastle. The shares rose 1.09 rand, or 1.8
percent, to 62.30 rand.  Control Instruments Group Ltd. (CNL)  : The maker of
electronic components for cars said its loss widened to 7.3
million rand for the six months ended June from 1.7 million rand
a year earlier. The shares climbed 5 cents, or 10 percent, to 55
cents.  Group Five Ltd. (GRF SJ): The South African construction
company releases full-year results. The shares gained 50 cents,
or 1.8 percent, to 28.51 rand.  Harmony Gold Mining Co Ltd. (HAR)  : Africa’s third-
largest producer of the metal releases second-quarter results.
The shares slid 2.99 rand, or 2.9 percent, to 99 rand.  Impala Platinum Holdings Ltd. (IMP)  : The world’s second-
largest producer of the metal offered wage increases of between
8 percent and 10 percent, the  National Union of Mineworkers 
said. The union will meet its members and make a decision this
week. The shares gained 1.94 rand, or 1.2 percent, to 169.07
rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of these South
African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) fell 0.4 percent to $19.65.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) dropped 4.3 percent to $43.82.
BHP Billiton Plc (BBL US) increased 1.4 percent to $65.55.
DRDGold Ltd. (DROOY US) climbed 2.5 percent to $4.57. Gold
Fields Ltd. (GFI US) slid 1.7 percent to $16.40. Harmony Gold
Mining Co. (HMY US) declined 3.5 percent to $13.95. Impala
Platinum Holdings (IMPUY US) was unchanged at $23.75. Sappi Ltd.
(SPP US) fell 3.3 percent to $3.52. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US)
increased 1.6 percent to $44.30.  The following stocks will begin trading without the right
to the latest dividend: Anglo American Plc (AGL SJ), Anglo
American Platinum Ltd. (AMS SJ), British American Tobacco Plc
(BTI SJ), Hudaco Industries Ltd. (HDC SJ), Kumba Iron Ore Ltd.
(KIO SJ), Mondi Ltd. (MND SJ), Mondi Plc (MNP SJ), Paladin
Capital Ltd. (PLD SJ), Sabvest Ltd. (SBV SJ).  To contact the reporter on this story:
